## 4. Checking if Home Directory Exists

Use `-d` flag inside `if` condition:

```bash
if [ -d "$homedir" ]; then
    echo "Home exists!"
else
    echo "Home missing!"
fi
```

| Flag | Meaning |
|---|---|
| `-d` | is a directory |
| `-f` | is a file |
| `-e` | exists (file or directory) |
| `-r` | is readable |
| `-w` | is writable |
| `-x` | is executable |

### Always quote variables in conditions!

```bash
# Wrong ❌ — breaks if path has spaces
if [ -d $homedir ]

# Correct ✅
if [ -d "$homedir" ]
```

