## 7. Key Concepts Summary

### Piping to while read:
```bash
# Single variable
command | while read line; do
    echo $line
done

# Multiple variables
command | while read var1 var2; do
    echo "$var1 and $var2"
done
```

### Always quote variables:
```bash
# In conditions
if [ -d "$homedir" ]
if [ -f "$filename" ]
if [ "$username" == "root" ]

# In commands
lastlog -u "$username"
ls "$homedir"
```

### awk with conditions:
```bash
# Numeric condition
awk '$3>=1000 {print $1}'      # UID >= 1000
awk '$3==0 {print $1}'         # only root
awk 'NR>1 {print $1}'          # skip header

# String condition
awk '$2=="**Never" {print $1}' # never logged in
awk '$7=="/bin/bash" {print $1}' # bash users only
```

